 dough to same size then place over filling. Use a rolling pin to lightly press layers together (removing air) and seal edges tightly. Make a few small holes in the top with a fork. Bake for 20 minutes (190°C) until lightly browned."},{"content":"Cut in diamonds using a knife or pizza cutter and serve warm drizzled with extra virgin olive oil."}],"hintsAndTricks":["Soparnik is a traditional Dalmatian dish. It was first considered for fasting or food for the poor, being made from a simple dough of plain flour, water, salt and a splash of olive oil then filled with chard. It is now declared as part of the cultural heritage of Croatia."],"basicInfo":["easy","20m","1h 45m","22 pieces"]}